item.title: RS Autoers supported on rs.com forums,rofl
item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

billygotshot:

they make the price go up

Iron ore has been 100gp for 3+ years. Autoers auto that.

billygotshot:

you use to actually be able to make money from high alching. now its impossible unless you get the stuff yourself and make the bow.

No, autoers make prices go DOWN, it’s lazy assholes that can’t be asked to cut 1k yews, or string 1k flax, or even craft 1k nats that make prices go up.

Let me explain something to you, if autoers get logs, more logs go into the economy, making them easier to buy, so if someone wants to be greedy and charge an extra 50gp per log, people can buy from someone else. In time, people offer less and less to try and sell their logs, as a result, logs go down in price because of autoers. Now, lets say autoers didn’t sell logs any more, less logs are going in to the economy so more people are forced to buy from less sellers, thus it’s easy for a seller to charge higher because they know all other sellers would go higher because people are greedy like that, so as a result of autoers not cutting yews, they go up in price.

Now, lets say a huge swarm of autoers cut yews, made bowstrings and made natures, and sold at high prices, because there are more sellers someone would be bound to sell cheaper to get rid of their stock, and as a result more legit people will sell cheaper so the autoers are forced to sell cheaper, and as a result, yew logs, nats and bowstrings will all go down in price. If it wasn’t for autoers, lazy people will charge MORE and MORE for raw materials to level a skill, like magic, easier.

High alch and make 16gp profit.
